# Indian Market Data Conventions

## NSE Symbol Formats (Kite)

```python
"NSE:RELIANCE"     # equity — always CAPS
"NSE:NIFTY 50"     # index — note the space, not NIFTY50
"NSE:NIFTY BANK"   # BankNifty index — not BANKNIFTY
"NSE:INDIA VIX"    # volatility index
"BSE:SENSEX"       # Sensex is on BSE, not NSE
"BSE:500325"       # BSE accepts scrip codes too
```

When no exchange prefix is given, default to `NSE`.

## Kite Instrument Token Cache

`kite.instruments(exchange)` downloads ~1MB and takes ~2s.
Always use `core/kite_client.get_instruments()` — it caches in memory per session.
Never call `kite.instruments()` directly inside a tool.

## Access Token

- Expires at end of each trading day (or at midnight)
- Stored in `.env` as `KITE_ACCESS_TOKEN`
- User generates it manually each morning
- If tools return auth errors, the token has expired — tell the user to refresh it

## NSE Public Data (Layer 2+)

FII/DII flows come from NSE's website, not Kite.
Use `nsepython` library for scraping — it handles NSE's anti-scraping headers.
Data is only available after ~7 PM IST for the current trading day.

## Market Hours

NSE/BSE: 09:15 AM – 03:30 PM IST, Monday–Friday
Pre-open: 09:00–09:15 AM IST
After-hours quotes may show stale prices — always note this in responses.

## F&O Expiry

Weekly: every Thursday (BankNifty, Nifty)
Monthly: last Thursday of the month
If Thursday is a holiday, expiry moves to Wednesday.
